headline: US High Growth Tech Stocks To Watch In Your Portfolio
summary: As the U.S. market navigates through fluctuating economic indicators and trade discussions, with key indices like the S&P 500 and Nasdaq Composite experiencing recent highs, investors are keenly observing high-growth tech stocks that could potentially offer robust returns amidst this dynamic environment. headline: The 3 Best-Performing S&P 500 Stocks of the Last 3 Years Have 1 Key Commonality Other Than Being AI Stocks. Can You Guess It?
summary: Palantir, Super Micro Computer, and Nvidia are the best-performing stocks on the S&P 500 index over the last three years.  The three best-performing stocks on the S&P 500 index over the past three years, as of June 30, are Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) with a 1,403% return; Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI), 1,116%; and Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA), 943%.
